[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA timeout error has been encountered during libFuzzer testing, indicating that the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer-generated input caused the program to exceed the maximum allowed execution [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtime. This suggests the presence of code that can be triggered to run for an [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessive duration, potentially indicating an algorithmic complexity issue, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite loop, or resource-intensive operation.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue manifests as a [0m[32m"libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m error, which occurs when libFuzzer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetects that processing a particular input has exceeded the configured timeout [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthreshold. This is a critical finding as it indicates that certain inputs can cause[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe program to hang or execute for an unreasonably long time.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**What the issue represents:**[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer discovered an input that causes the target program to execute beyond [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe timeout limit [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtypically several seconds to minutes, depending on [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This behavior indicates potential algorithmic complexity problems, such as [0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[39mn²[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor worse time complexity on certain inputs[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout could also indicate the presence of unbounded loops, recursion [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout proper termination conditions, or expensive operations without input [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Key observations:**[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is a denial-of-service [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability category, where an attacker could[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially craft inputs to make the system unresponsive[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The issue is reproducible with specific fuzzer-generated inputs[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout mechanism in libFuzzer successfully detected the anomaly, preventing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindefinite hanging[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Areas requiring investigation:**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo obtain a comprehensive understanding of this timeout issue, the following [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents should be examined:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Input Processing Logic**: The code paths that handle and parse incoming data, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparticularly where the fuzzer input enters the system[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Loop Constructs**: All loops [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor, while, do-while[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that process input data, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking for proper termination conditions and bounds[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Recursive Functions**: Any recursive algorithms that operate on [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muser-controlled data, verifying depth limits and base cases[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Algorithm Complexity**: Functions with nested iterations or operations that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscale non-linearly with input size[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Resource-Intensive Operations**: Database queries, file I/O, network [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations, or cryptographic functions that might be called without proper input [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **State Machine Implementations**: Code that maintains state across multiple [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations, which could enter infinite state transitions[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Parser and Deserialization Code**: Components that process structured data [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformats [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJSON, XML, protocol buffers, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m which might have pathological cases[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe investigation should focus on identifying which specific input patterns trigger[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe timeout and tracing the execution path to locate the bottleneck or infinite [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe evaluation report indicates a **libFuzzer timeout error**, which means the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer discovered an input that causes the program to execute beyond the timeout [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthreshold. This is a critical denial-of-service [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets, I've identified **three distinct [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerabilities** that can cause timeout issues in the Type1 font parser:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Causes Identified:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Vulnerability [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInfinite Loop in readEncoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** - Lines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[39m of [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mType1Parser.java[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A while loop with negated condition lacks null checking[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When EOF is reached unexpectedly, `[0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns null[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mpeekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns false [0m[1;39m([0m[39msince aheadToken is null[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The negation `![0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse && [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` evaluates to true, causing infinite loop[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` keeps returning null indefinitely[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Vulnerability [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInfinite Loop in parseBinary[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** - Lines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[39m of [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mType1Parser.java[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Identical pattern to Vulnerability [0m[1;36m3[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Searches for [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[39m literal but enters infinite loop on malformed input[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Same root cause: negated condition with no null check[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Vulnerability [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMemory Exhaustion in readCharString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** - Line [0m[1;36m507[0m[39m of [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mType1Lexer.java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Unchecked allocation based on user-controlled `length` parameter[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Attacker can provide extremely large values [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., Integer.MAX_VALUE[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Causes OutOfMemoryError or hangs during allocation attempt[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No validation before `new byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mlength[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Insights from Code Analysis:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase demonstrates **both correct and incorrect patterns**:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Correct patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfound in readProc, readSimpleDict, readSubrs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Explicit null checks: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m throw/break; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Positive loop conditions that naturally exit when [0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is null[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Using [0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m utility methods that throw IOException on null[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Incorrect patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvulnerabilities [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m & [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Negated conditions: `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No null checking in loop body[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Direct calls to `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without validation[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Fix Infinite Loop in [0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mVulnerability [0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.java` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Change:** Add null check inside the while loop body to detect EOF and throw [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current vulnerable code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"readonly"[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Fixed code:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"readonly"[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                || [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Should have found dup, readonly or def?! EOF?"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification:**[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Follows the pattern from parseBinary lines [0m[1;36m556[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m564[0m[39m where null is explicitly [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecked[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Minimal change that doesn't alter the parsing logic[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throws IOException which is already expected by callers[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Error message is consistent with similar checks in the codebase[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Fix Infinite Loop in [0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mVulnerability [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.java` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Change:** Add null check inside the while loop body to detect EOF and throw [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current vulnerable code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.LITERAL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        && [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Fixed code:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.LITERAL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        && [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"EOF? Should have found CharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification:**[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Identical pattern to Patch [0m[1;36m1[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents infinite loop when CharStrings dictionary is missing[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintains consistency with other null checks in the codebase[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Minimal, surgical change that doesn't affect valid font parsing[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Fix Memory Exhaustion in [0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mVulnerability [0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Lexer.java`[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Changes:** [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE constant at class level [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m50[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Add length validation in [0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method before allocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore line [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m507[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Add at class level [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m, after other fields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static final int MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE = 1_000_000;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m In readCharString method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m502[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m515[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add validation before allocation:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate Token [0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Add this validation BEFORE the try block:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength > MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mDamagedFontException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"char string is too long. [0m[32mlength[0m[32m="[0m[39m +[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                length + [0m[32m" [0m[32mmax_length[0m[32m="[0m[39m + MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    try[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mbuffer.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m space[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m data = new byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mlength[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mbuffer.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return new [0m[1;35mToken[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, Token.CHARSTRING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBufferUnderflowException exception[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Premature end of buffer reached"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification:**[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- 1MB [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is a reasonable limit for charstring data[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Legitimate Type1 charstrings are typically a few hundred bytes[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses existing DamagedFontException class [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready imported and used elsewhere[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents both OutOfMemoryError and allocation hangs[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fails fast with clear error message before attempting allocation[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Comprehensive Explanation[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Minimal, Surgical Changes**: Each fix is a [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m line addition that doesn't [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malter the core parsing logic[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Follows Existing Patterns**: The null checks mirror the correct patterns [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready used in [0m[1;35mreadProc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadSimpleDict[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and the beginning of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: The fixes only add safety checks without changing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhow valid fonts are parsed[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Consistent Error Handling**: Uses IOException [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready expected by all [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcallers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and DamagedFontException [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready used in the codebase[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Addresses All Timeout Causes**: Fixes both infinite loop scenarios and memory [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexhaustion that can cause timeouts[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Functionality[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Valid Type1 fonts** will continue to parse exactly as before because:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - They contain the expected tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"def"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Their charstring sizes are reasonable [0m[1;39m([0m[39m< 1MB[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The null checks only trigger on malformed/truncated input[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Error handling** remains consistent:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Throws IOException for parsing errors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexpected by callers[0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Uses DamagedFontException for corrupt font data [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready handled[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **API compatibility** is maintained:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - No method signature changes[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - No new public methods or classes[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Same exception types thrown[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Issues[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Prevents Timeout from Infinite Loops**: The null checks break the loops [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately when EOF is reached unexpectedly, throwing IOException instead of [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlooping forever[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Prevents Timeout from Memory Exhaustion**: The size limit prevents allocation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhangs and OutOfMemoryError, failing fast with a clear error message[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Prevents DoS Attacks**: Malicious fonts can no longer hang the parser [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindefinitely or exhaust memory[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential Side Effect**: Some edge-case malformed fonts that previously caused [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhangs will now throw exceptions earlier[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: This is actually desired behavior - failing fast is better than [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhanging. The error messages clearly indicate what was expected.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential Side Effect**: Very large [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbut legitimate[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m charstrings exceeding 1MB [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwould be rejected[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: 1MB is conservative - real Type1 charstrings are much smaller. If [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate fonts are found with larger charstrings, the constant can be increased.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Reference to Similar Solutions[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe code analysis reveals multiple examples of the correct pattern already in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m556[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m564[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparseBinary[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Correct null checking with explicit variable[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m334[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m336[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m344[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m346[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadSimpleDict[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Multiple null checks in loops[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m476[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m478[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadProc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Null check with IOException throw[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m515[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m517[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadProcVoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Same pattern as readProc[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m719[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m721[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Null check with break[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fixes align with these established patterns, ensuring consistency across the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Testing Considerations[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying these patches:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Valid Type1 fonts [0m[1;39m([0m[39m.pfb files[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should parse without issues[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Malformed fonts will throw IOException with descriptive messages[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzing should no longer trigger timeout errors[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Existing unit tests should continue to pass[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fixes address the root causes identified in PDFBOX-[0m[1;36m5624[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmentioned in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39manalysis[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing process using libFuzzer encountered a timeout error. This indicates [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat during the parsing of Type1 font data, the code execution either:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Enters an infinite or very long-running loop[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe error occurs within the fontbox component, specifically in the Type1 font [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing functionality.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch made three distinct modifications to the codebase:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Type1Parser.java - Line [0m[1;36m222[0m[39m modification:**[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Before:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading phase, throwing an IOException if the token is null.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Type1Parser.java - Line [0m[1;36m646[0m[39m modification:**[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Before:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis change adds a similar null check while searching for the [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[39m literal[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the font data.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Type1Lexer.java - CharString size validation:**[0m                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid negative CharString length: "[0m[39m + length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength > MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"CharString length "[0m[39m + length + [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[32m" exceeds maximum allowed size of "[0m[39m + MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis adds bounds checking for CharString length to prevent excessively large [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocations or processing.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Post-Patch Result[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the libFuzzer timeout error continues to occur. This [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates that:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout is not caused by the specific conditions addressed in the patch[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The infinite loop or long-running operation occurs in a different location[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The malformed input causing the timeout bypasses the newly added checks[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Type1Parser.java loop structures:**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The while loop at line [0m[1;36m219[0m[39m that checks for [0m[32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, or [0m[32m"def"[0m[39m tokens[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The while loop at line [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m that searches for [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[39m literal[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any other loop structures in the parsing logic that might not have proper [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtermination conditions[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Type1Lexer.java tokenization:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The token reading mechanisms, particularly `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementations[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Buffer operations that might read indefinitely without proper bounds checking[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35mreadCharString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method's actual byte reading logic after the validation [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Token peek/next interaction:**[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The condition checking logic using `[0m[1;35mpeekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that might [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: * The Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font format is a free-text format which is somewhat difficult[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * to parse. This is made worse by the fact that many Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font files do[0m       [2m                [0m
