[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter reviewing the evaluation report and code snippets, I've identified the root [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause of the timeout issue:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Core Problem[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout is caused by **three unbounded while loops** in Type1Parser that search[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor specific token patterns without any iteration limits:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `[0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Searches for NAME tokens with text [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, or [0m[32m"def"[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Searches for LITERAL token with text [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"CharStrings"[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m557[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m564[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Searches for token with text [0m[32m"Private"[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese loops will iterate through the entire token stream until they find the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected patterns. With malformed fuzzer input containing large amounts of data [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat never produces the expected tokens, these loops can run millions of times [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcausing timeouts.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why Previous Patch Failed[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch added null checks after calling `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in two of these [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m222[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m643[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but this doesn't prevent infinite loops. The null check [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly triggers when the buffer is completely exhausted, meaning the loop has already[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterated through the entire large malformed input, consuming excessive time.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Correct Solution Pattern[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase consistently uses **bounded for loops with predefined lengths** for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructured data parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mseen in `[0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadCharStrings[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadSimpleDict[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mparseASCII[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. These loops:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Have maximum iteration counts[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Include premature end detection[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Break early when expected patterns aren't found[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe three problematic while loops are outliers that violate this pattern.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Add Maximum Iteration Limit Constant[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a constant in `Type1Parser.java` to define the maximum number of tokens to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msearch through when looking for expected patterns. This should be generous enough [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor legitimate fonts but prevent timeouts on malformed input:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static final int MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS = [0m[1;36m10000[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis constant should be added near the existing constants [0m[1;39m([0m[39mEEXEC_KEY, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCHARSTRING_KEY around lines [0m[1;36m44[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m45[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Convert Unbounded While Loop #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadEncoding - lines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReplace the unbounded while loop with a bounded loop that tracks iterations:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Initialize an iteration counter before the loop[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Increment the counter inside the loop[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Check if counter exceeds MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS and throw IOException[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep all existing null checks from the previous patch[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintain the same loop condition logic[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Convert Unbounded While Loop #[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparseBinary - lines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApply the same pattern:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add iteration counter before the loop[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Increment counter inside the loop  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throw IOException if limit exceeded[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep existing null check from previous patch[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Preserve loop condition checking for CharStrings literal[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Convert Unbounded While Loop #[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparseBinary - lines [0m[1;36m557[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m564[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis loop already has null checking in the condition and after the loop, but still [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeds iteration limiting:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add iteration counter before the loop[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Increment counter inside the loop[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throw IOException if limit exceeded before the existing null check[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep all existing null handling logic[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Preserve Previous Patch Elements[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch added two important safety checks that must be retained:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**In Type1Parser.java:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m222[0m[39m: Null check after `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in readEncoding loop[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m643[0m[39m: Null check after `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in parseBinary CharStrings search loop[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**In Type1Lexer.java:**[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE constant [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m54[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Negative length check in readCharString [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m508[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m511[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maximum size check in readCharString [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m516[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAll these checks provide defense-in-depth and should be preserved.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Implementation Details[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### For Loop #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadEncoding - lines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBefore the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m217[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add: int searchIterations = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInside the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m[1;36m221[0m[39m, before line [0m[1;36m222[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add iteration check:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++searchIterations > MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Exceeded maximum search iterations while reading [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mencoding"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKeep the existing null check from previous patch after [0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### For Loop #[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparseBinary - lines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBefore the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m640[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add: int searchIterations = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInside the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m[1;36m642[0m[39m, before line [0m[1;36m643[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add iteration check:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++searchIterations > MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Exceeded maximum search iterations while searching for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mCharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKeep the existing null check from previous patch after [0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### For Loop #[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparseBinary - lines [0m[1;36m557[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m564[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBefore the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m557[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add: int searchIterations = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInside the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m[1;36m561[0m[39m, before line [0m[1;36m562[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add iteration check:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++searchIterations > MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Exceeded maximum search iterations while searching for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mPrivate dictionary"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKeep all existing null handling logic[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is Optimal[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses Root Cause**: Directly limits iterations in the exact loops causing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeouts, rather than trying to prevent symptoms[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves Lenient Parsing**: The comments in Type1Parser explain it's designed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto be [0m[32m"as forgiving as possible"[0m[39m for non-conforming fonts. Adding iteration limits [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaintains this leniency while preventing abuse[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Follows Established Patterns**: Matches the bounded loop pattern used [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthroughout the codebase in methods like `[0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mreadCharStrings[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadSimpleDict[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Combines with previous patch's null checks and size limits[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor multiple layers of protection[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Appropriate Limit**: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m iterations is generous for legitimate fonts [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtypically have structured sections with explicit lengths[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but prevents [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmillion-iteration timeouts on malformed input[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Minimal Code Changes**: Only adds counters and checks to three specific loops [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout restructuring the parsing logic[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Loop conditions remain unchanged[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Token reading and checking logic is identical[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing safety checks are preserved[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The only addition is iteration counting with bounds checking[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Normal fonts will never hit the limits[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses Issues[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Initial timeout**: The iteration limits prevent unbounded loops from running [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindefinitely on malformed input[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Post-patch timeout**: Unlike the previous patch which only checked for null [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mwhich happens after full buffer exhaustion[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, this patch prevents excessive [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations before full exhaustion[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential Side Effect**: Highly unusual but legitimate fonts with thousands of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munexpected tokens before expected markers could be rejected.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m iteration limit is extremely generous - legitimate Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m fonts use [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructured declarations with explicit lengths[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If real-world fonts are rejected, the constant can be adjusted upward[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error messages clearly indicate the issue, making debugging straightforward[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe bounded loop pattern with iteration limits is used throughout fontbox:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses for loop with declared array size[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mreadCharStrings[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses for loop with declared dict size[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mparseASCII[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses for loop with declared font dict size[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All these methods also include premature end detection[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix applies the same proven pattern to the outlier while loops.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [33mtid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x000055fa07fcb300[0m[39m [0m[33mnid[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0x22[0m[39m waiting on condition  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNI global refs: [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m, weak refs: [0m[1;36m0[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===[0m[33mIssue[0m[39m===[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a libFuzzer timeout error occurring during fuzzing of the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApache PDFBox/FontBox codebase. A patch was attempted to address this by adding [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miteration limits to several search loops in the Type1Parser class and size limits [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto CharString reading in the Type1Lexer class. However, the patch failed to compile[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdue to a variable redeclaration error where the variable `searchIterations` was [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclared multiple times within the same method scope in Type1Parser.java.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue manifests as a libFuzzer timeout error, which typically occurs [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen the fuzzer encounters code that executes for an excessive amount of time [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout completing. This suggests that somewhere in the codebase, there are loops [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor operations that can run indefinitely or for an unreasonably long period when [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing certain malformed or adversarial input data. The issue is reported [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout specific details about which input triggered the timeout or which code path[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas being executed.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempts to address potential infinite loop scenarios in two files:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Type1Parser.java modifications:**[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Introduces a constant `MAX_SEARCH_ITERATIONS = [0m[1;36m10000[0m[39m` to limit the number of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations in search loops[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Adds iteration counting and bounds checking in three different locations:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Around line [0m[1;36m220[0m[39m: In a loop searching for [0m[32m"dup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"readonly"[0m[39m, or [0m[32m"def"[0m[39m tokens [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile reading encoding[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Around line [0m[1;36m568[0m[39m: In a loop searching for the [0m[32m"Private"[0m[39m dictionary token[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Around line [0m[1;36m656[0m[39m: In a loop searching for the [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[39m literal token[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Each protected loop includes:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - An `searchIterations` counter variable[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A check that throws an IOException when the maximum iteration count is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceeded[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additional null checks on `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls with appropriate error messages[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Type1Lexer.java modifications:**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Introduces a constant `MAX_CHAR_STRING_SIZE = 1_000_000` to limit CharString [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Adds validation in the `readCharString` method to:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check for negative length values[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check for lengths exceeding the maximum allowed size[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throw IOException with descriptive messages for invalid inputs[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Compilation Error[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch fails to compile with the following error:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/project-parent/pdfbox/fontbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/[0m[95mType1Pars[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95mer.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m656[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m13[0m[1;39m][0m[39m variable searchIterations is already defined in method [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis error indicates that the variable `searchIterations` is declared multiple [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimes within the same method `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. Looking at the patch, there are[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthree separate locations where `int searchIterations = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` is declared:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- At line [0m[1;36m220[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfirst occurrence[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- At line [0m[1;36m568[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39msecond occurrence[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- At line [0m[1;36m656[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthird occurrence[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAll three declarations appear to be within the same method scope, causing the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation failure. The patch author likely intended to use separate scopes or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdifferent variable names for each loop's iteration counter.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a complete understanding of the timeout issue and develop a proper fix, the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfollowing areas should be investigated:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Method Scope Analysis in [0m[1;35mType1Parser.parseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Examine the complete [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure of the `[0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to understand:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The scope boundaries and whether these loops are in nested or sequential [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontexts[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether these loops can be refactored into separate methods with their own [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscopes[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The relationships between these three search loops and whether they can share [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcounter logic[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Loop Termination Conditions**: Analyze each of the three identified loops to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What conditions are supposed to cause normal termination[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Why these conditions might not be met with certain inputs[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether there are missing validation checks for malformed input[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The expected structure of valid Type1 font files[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Token Stream Handling**: Investigate the Type1Lexer implementation to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How tokens are generated and buffered[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the lexer can produce infinite token streams with certain inputs[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The behavior of `[0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and `[0m[1;35mpeekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods with [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed data[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **CharString Size Limitations**: Review the `readCharString` method and related [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode to verify:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the 1MB limit is appropriate for legitimate font files[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How CharString lengths are determined from the input[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether there are other size-related vulnerabilities in binary data reading[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Error Recovery Mechanisms**: Assess the broader error handling strategy:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How the parser recovers from or reports malformed input[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether throwing IOExceptions is the appropriate strategy for fuzzing [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscenarios[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The impact of these exceptions on calling code[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Test Coverage**: Examine existing test cases to understand:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What types of malformed inputs are currently tested[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether there are regression tests for timeout scenarios[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How the fuzzing harness integrates with the codebase[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m: * Parses an Adobe Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m.pfb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m font. It is used exclusively by Type1Font.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: * The Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font format is a free-text format which is somewhat difficult[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * to parse. This is made worse by the fact that many Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font files do[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: * The Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font format is a free-text format which is somewhat difficult[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * to parse. This is made worse by the fact that many Type [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m font files do[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m: * @see [0m[32m"Adobe Type 1 Font Format, Adobe Systems [0m[32m([0m[32m1999[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m                         [2m                [0m
